fields.description:
As a user, I'd like to search for ranges of Parent Links instead of adding all the parent links separetaly. 

When searching for all subtasks in Jira, we have to use a JQL like below:
* Option 1
{code}
"Parent Link" = ABC-123 OR "Parent Link" = ABC-124 OR "Parent Link" = ABC-125 OR "Parent Link" = ABC-126
{code}
* Option 2
{code}
"Parent Link" in (ABC-123, ABC-124, ABC-125, ABC-126)
{code}

h3. Suggestion
Add a *between* or other comparison clause to JQL searches so we can use link below:
{code}
"Parent Link" between (ABC-123, ABC-126)
{code}
{code}
"Parent Link" >= ABC-123 OR "Parent Link" <= ABC-126
{code}
